$interpreted: Sanchez: General! You've come back!
Sanchez: General! I'm innocent! I'm begging you to let me go!
Lazer: ...Quite determined. Uncuff them.
Sanchez: Thank...thank you! Scum, thank the General!
Lazer: You...want to leave?
Sanchez: Yuh...Yes! Yes!
Lazer: If you can defeat me, then you can go.
Sanchez: D...De...Def...Defeat...? Are you serious?
Lazer: You. Must. Defeat. Me.
Lazer: All you need to do is win, and you can leave immediately.
Sanchez: How...why...I wouldn't dare touch the General.
Lazer: Then you stay. But you...
Lazer: Huh?
Rune: ...Huh? What's on...my body?
Lazer: These tattoos...
Lazer: ...The slave class of the Desert...has all sorts of beings...
Lazer: Tattooed fellow. Would you like to try?
Rune: ...Fight.
Rune: Can...not...win...
Sanchez: Enough! That you're still alive is itself impressive!
Sanchez: ...Wait. Trash, you're not injured?
Lazer: Interesting. Far from it.
Lazer: Lock them up.
Sanchez: General──！
Lazer: If you want to live, you have one more choice. If you accept, then I'll let you go.
Sanchez: Yes, sir! General, whatever you want!
Lazer: Listen carefully.
Lazer: I want you...
Diana: ...I'm tired. I'll rest early. You go ahead first.
Head House-maid: Order received, Your Highness.
Diana: Being alone is always the most relaxing...
Diana: ...Who's there?
Diana: Lazer?
Lazer: It's me.
Diana: ...You scared me.
Lazer: ...Your Majesty the Queen seems rather disappointed that it is I who have come to see her.
Diana: It's a little late. Is something the matter?
Lazer: Actually, yes. Your Majesty, if I may...
Diana: You want those two to be the first to fight in the Colosseum?
Lazer: Yes. And the traditional rules must be upheld.
Diana: "The victor shall be pardoned of their crime, and granted their complete freedom"...that's their only chance of survival.
Diana: But Lazer, you're the only one...who has ever succeeded.
Lazer: ......
Diana: Lazer, I don't want the Colosseum to be reopened. If Devious hadn't threatened me with what happened at the hatchery...
Lazer: I, your servant, understand. Your Highness made a wise decision, given the circumstances.
Diana: ......
Diana: ...Do I hear a bit of sarcasm in your voice?
Lazer: I, your servant, merely feel it will be an interesting sight.
Diana: ...Interesting?
Lazer: ...Child, if I'm not mistaken,
Lazer: that tattooed fellow has as much of a chance as I once did.
Diana: ...Godfather, what are you thinking?
Lazer: Your Highness, the Queen, your servant is thinking...
Lazer: To see Devious and those barbaric nobles disappointed...though the chance may be small, it's worth a try.
